summary: Adds birds to the world of skyrim
descriptionHtml:
[img]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/images/17723-1-1339238620.png[/img]
Logo made by psychosteve. Thanks a lot 8) 

_______________________________________________________________________________

[b]18.08.12 - Birds of Skyrim version 0.6.5 released. 

Changes in this update:
- Some new bird spawns around skyrim
- Small bugfix (thanks Eyatorius!) 
- Introducing sound effects. 

Seagull sounds have now been added to these three locations: 

- Solitude docks
- The Dainty sload (Ship)
- Wreck of the brinehammer

Feel free to give feedback, critisism, endorsements, suggestions etc ;) 

As always, test the new update before you continue your savegame!

Enjoy!
 [/b]
_______________________________________________________________________________

[b]09.08.12 - New textures for the default chicken has been uploaded. There is a brown, and a white variant. Copy data folder into skyrim folder to install. This can also be used together with automatic variants. [/b]

_______________________________________________________________________________


[b]Description[/b]

This is a part of an ongoing project aiming to populate skyrim with much more diverse wildlife. I hope to be able to improve all aspects of animal life in the future. 


[b]Bird locations: [/b]

[b]Bullfinch:[/b] Found outside the farms in windhelm, and in dawnstar. 
[b]Crows[/b]: Found outside the college of winterhold, and in Windhelm. 
[b]Jay:[/b] Found in falkreath
[b]Kingfisher:[/b] Found near inland water sources. For example the water west of riverwood
[b]Oystercatcher[/b]: Found on the northwestern coast. 
[b]Pheasant[/b]: Mostly found in the wilderness between Riverwood and Falkreath. 
[b]Pigeons[/b]: Found inside and around the cities Markhart, Riften, Solitude, Whiterun and windhelm. 
[b]Wood pigeons[/b]: Found in falkhreath and outside Markhart
[b]Pine thrush[/b]: Found in the rift area. 
[b]Sandpipers:[/b] Found in the swampy area east of solitude.
[b]Seagulls[/b]: Found on the dock areas of Dawnstar, Morthal, Solitude and Windhelm. They are  also found in the wild along the northern coast of Skyrim. 
[b]Red grouse and ruffed grouse[/b]: Found on the plains between Whiterun and Roerikstead. 
[b]Sprouced grouse[/b]: Found in the wilderness between Riverwood and Falkreath
[b]Semi coloured grouse[/b]: Found in the border area between snowland and dryland. 
[b]White grouse[/b]: Found in the wild in snowy areas. Hard to find, and rare. 
[b]Snow bunting[/b]: Found in winterhold.
[b]Sparrows, willow tits and great tits[/b]: Different places around skyrim
[b]Ravens[/b]: Mostly found east of Whiterun. You could for example try the riften graveyard.
[b]Roosters[/b]: Most of the farms around skyrim have one rooster. 
[b]Baby chicken[/b]: Riverwood, Ivarstead, Solitude farm, and Whiterun farm


[b]Installation[/b]

Copy content of compressed folder to the skyrim folder. 


[b]For rooster sounds download this mod: [/b]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=17257]Roosters at dawn[/url]

[b]Other animal mods highly recommended by me:[/b]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=10175]Skytest - Realistic animals and predators[/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=8565]More village animals[/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=14320]Improved fish - more spawning[/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=4955]101BugsHD[/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=17424]Pets of Skyrim[/url]

All of them are compatible with my mod, and will together with this mod make your skyrim a much richer place!


[b]Birds of skyrim international: [/b]

[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/20150]Brazilian Portuguese[/url] (V0.6)
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/18120]Czech[/url] (V0.6)
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/28547]French[/url] (V0.6.5)
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/22921]German[/url] (V0.6.5)
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/19058]Italian[/url] (V0.6.5)
[url=http://modgames.net/load/305-1-0-12085]Russian[/url] (V0.5)
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/23340]Spanish[/url] (V0.6.5)



[b]I hope you guys enjoy![/b]


[youtube]WYogZto_ZTE[/youtube]

[youtube]Ww2cPPlnjG8[/youtube]

[youtube]WNeG0W3muW0[/youtube]

[youtube]hMOSo5LTy8c[/youtube]


[b]Further information: [/b]

This is a work in progress mod, so everything is not perfect yet. However i believe this mod is good enough to add something to the game. 

Below i have written down info on progress, and my own thoughts on direction of the mod: 

[b]BIRDS[/b]

Basically i am only adding birds that are a realistic and believable in the skyrim climate. Also, i will only base my birds on real world birds. No fantasy stuff :) 

My birds are coming from these ideas: 
- Found in Norway (I consider norwegian climate to match skyrim climate very well, also these are the birds i live with). 
- Found in tes lore. 
- Suggestions from users. 

Below is a list to give an idea of birds to come. 

[b]Confirmed birds to be in the next update 0.6 (search on google images to know what they look like):[/b]

- Female pheasants
- Magpies
- Wood pigeons

If you have any strong objections against any birds you are free to comment, but you have to bring good arguments :p 

[b]Birds that will be made sometime:[/b]
- Rock Warbler

[b]Birds i really want to add but I need to overcome technical difficulties:[/b]

- Swimming seagulls and ducks. 
- Owls
- Geese
- More customized flying birds, sizes and flying patterns. 

[b]Birds that already has been suggested and will be considered:[/b]

- Vultures (Bearded, Lappet, Black, Turkey, Condor, etc.)
- Eagles (Golden, Bald, African Crowned, Harpy, etc.)
- Owls (Great Horned, Snow, Eurasianed, Blakinston\'s, etc.) 
- Cranes (Whooping, Sarus, Red Crowned, etc.)
- Turkeys
- Falcons (Gyrfalcon, Peregrine, Kestrels, etc.)
- Hawks (Red-tailed, Cooper\'s, Kites, Osprey, etc.)
- Bats
- Blue Jays 
- Mocking Birds
- Atlantic Puffins
- Penguins

[b]Birds that have been suggested but will never make it to this mod:[/b]
- Parrots
- Any fantasy based creature

If your bird did not make it to one of these lists, i propably have missed it. Feel free to put it into comments section.

[b]FEATURES[/b]

[b]Features i am currently looking to implement (dont know when): [/b]
- Spesific sound effect for the birds. First will be seagullsounds in places with a lot of seagull. 
- 3D placement. I am trying to work out a good way of placing birds on shopsigns, lanterns, trees, roofs etc. 
- A good faction and ai behaviour system. 
- Bird spesific loot

[b]Features that have been suggested and i am considering:[\\b]

- Bird shit! :p 


[b]My other mod: [/b]

[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=17424]Pets of Skyrim[/url]

files.name: Birds of skyrim 025
files.changelogHtml:
New rooster and baby chicken models.
Some ai tweaking

files.name: Birds of Skyrim 03
files.changelogHtml:
- New flying models for ravens and seagulls
- New grouse model, with new texture variations
- Much more extensive spawning, a large part of skyrim is now affected by this mod

files.name: Birds of Skyrim 04
files.changelogHtml:
New sparrow, great tit, spruce grouse and pheasant.
Improved seagull textures
More spawns around skyrim

files.name: Birds of Skyrim 05
files.changelogHtml:
New bullfinch, pinetrush, jay, oystercatcher and sandpiper
Introducing navmesh on objects, making the birds standing on top of things
Converted mod to bsa archive, for easier install/uninstall
Edited and new spawns around Skyrim
Small tweaks in ai, still not finished.

files.name: Birds of Skyrim 06_BSA archive
files.changelogHtml:
New birds added: Ravens on the ground, two variants of female pheasants, magpies, kingfishers, two variations of starling, semi coloured grouse, snow bunting, willow tits and wood pigeons
Ai tweaks
Removed hawks circling above Solitude docks.
Many new spawns around Skyrim
